The present study revealed that there are some difficulties
with TB infection control measures at a general hospital in
Hanoi, including poor understanding self-protection using
an N95 respirator and immediate isolation of patients with
suspected TB. A high prevalence of latent TB infection
among health professionals was observed, in particular
those in the emergency department. Providing educational
programs and obtaining knowledge from scientific sources
